      "message": "Yeah, I went back and forth on that. Points/counterpoints:\n\n1) There are other failure conditions where I just sort of fail without an error today. I really want to make those bail (probably switch to having run return bool), and that would fit well here too...\n\nbut...\n\n2) This mimics what happens on a GPU. I don\u0027t know that access is actually pinned like this, but it\u0027s at least defined to keep running and produce *something*. We don\u0027t have to be constrained by that, though.\n\nI think to ignore dead lanes, it ends up being something like:\n\nif (skvx::any(mask() \u0026 (sp[0].fSigned \u003e 0) \u0026 (sp[0].fSigned \u003c length))) { abort(); }",
